                    <div class="excel-upload font-styling" id="subjects-upload">
                        <h1><i class="fa-solid fa-2"></i> | CSV Files Upload Guide</h1>
                        <p>
                            These <b>CSV files</b> are used to configure subjects and lock attendance rules for
                            students.
                            Please follow the format carefully. Even small deviations can cause upload failures.
                        </p>

                        <h2>CSV File Structure Overview</h2>
                        <p>
                            Each CSV file must contain headers in the first row. Subjects inside cells should be
                            <b>comma-separated</b>.
                        </p>

                        <p><b>Common CSV Headers:</b></p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>class</b> – Class number (school) or department code (college)</li>
                            <li><b>majors</b> – Compulsory / common subjects</li>
                            <li><b>optionals</b> – Stream-based or elective subjects</li>
                            <li><b>minors</b> – Minor subjects, if applicable</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>School Use Case</h2>

                        <h3>Classes 1–8 (Primary & Middle School)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Class:</b> Enter the class number (e.g. 5, 6, 7)</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> All compulsory subjects for the class</li>
                            <li><b>Optionals / Minors:</b> Enter only if your school offers them</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p><b>Sample CSV:</b></p>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>class</th>
                                    <th>majors</th>
                                    <th>optionals</th>
                                    <th>minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>5</td>
                                    <td>English Language, English Literature, Mathematics, Science, Social Science</td>
                                    <td>Hindi, Bengali, Computer Applications</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <h3>Classes 9–10 (Stream-Based Structure)</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Class:</b> Enter 9 or 10</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> Subjects common to all streams</li>
                            <li><b>Optionals:</b> Stream-specific subjects</li>
                            <li><b>Minors:</b> Usually not applicable</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p>
                            <b class="tip">
                                Example: If <em>English Language</em> and <em>English Literature</em> are common across
                                all
                                streams, they go into <b>Majors</b>. Physics, Accounts, History, etc. go into
                                <b>Optionals</b>.
                            </b>
                        </p>

                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>class</th>
                                    <th>majors</th>
                                    <th>optionals</th>
                                    <th>minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>10</td>
                                    <td>English Language, English Literature, Physical Training, Games</td>
                                    <td>Physics, Chemistry, Mathematics, Biology, History, Geography, Accounts</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <p>
                            <b class="error">
                                NOTE: If PT or Games attendance is required, they <u>must</u> be included in the
                                <b>Majors</b> column. Otherwise, attendance will not be recorded.
                            </b>
                        </p>

                        <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Do not add stream-specific subjects to <b>Majors</b> for Classes 9–10.</li>
                            <li>Do not leave the <b>Majors</b> column empty.</li>
                            <li>Do not create multiple rows for different streams of the same class.</li>
                            <li>Subjects inside a cell must be comma-separated, not line-separated.</li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>College Use Case</h2>
                        <p>
                            College CSV files are department-based and cumulative across semesters.
                        </p>

                        <ul>
                            <li><b>Class:</b> Department short code (CSE, EEE, EE, IT, ME, etc.)</li>
                            <li><b>Majors:</b> All compulsory subjects from 1st to final semester (common to all
                                students)</li>
                            <li><b>Optionals:</b> All elective subjects across all semesters</li>
                            <li><b>Minors:</b> Minor subjects, if applicable</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p><b>Sample CSV:</b></p>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>class</th>
                                    <th>majors</th>
                                    <th>optionals</th>
                                    <th>minors</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>IT</td>
                                    <td>Programming Fundamentals, OOP, Data Structures, DBMS, OS, Computer Networks, Web
                                        Technologies</td>
                                    <td>AI, ML, Cloud Computing, Cyber Security</td>
                                    <td>Mathematics, Management Studies</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <p class="tip">
                            Tip: Do <b>not</b> split subjects semester-wise in CSV. The system automatically maps them
                            during attendance processing.
                        </p>
                        <p class="tip">
                            Tip: Do not remove any column from the CSV. If a field is not applicable to your
                            organization, keep the column and leave its value empty.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="font-styling" id="schedule-upload">
                        <h1><i class="fa-solid fa-3"></i> | Schedule CSV Upload Guide</h1>

                        <p>
                            This CSV file is used to configure <b>daily check-in and check-out schedules</b> for your
                            organization.
                            Each day can have a <b>day shift</b> and an optional <b>night shift</b>.
                        </p>

                        <h2>CSV File Structure</h2>
                        <p>
                            The CSV file must contain the following headers exactly as shown.
                            Header names are case-insensitive.
                        </p>

                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>Column</th>
                                    <th>Description</th>
                                    <th>Required</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>day</td>
                                    <td>Day of the week (Monday–Sunday)</td>
                                    <td>Yes</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>day_check_in</td>
                                    <td>Day shift check-in time (HH:MM)</td>
                                    <td>Yes</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>day_check_out</td>
                                    <td>Day shift check-out time (HH:MM)</td>
                                    <td>Yes</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>night_check_in</td>
                                    <td>Night shift check-in time (HH:MM)</td>
                                    <td>No</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>night_check_out</td>
                                    <td>Night shift check-out time (HH:MM)</td>
                                    <td>No</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>grace</td>
                                    <td>Grace period in minutes (0–60)</td>
                                    <td>Yes</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <h2>Valid Values & Rules</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                <b>day</b> must be one of:
                                <em>Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday</em>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Each day can appear <b>only once</b> in the CSV.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Time format must be <b>24-hour HH:MM</b> (e.g. 09:30, 17:45).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>Night shift is optional</b>, but if provided, both
                                <b>night_check_in</b> and <b>night_check_out</b> must be filled.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>grace</b> must be a number between <b>0 and 60</b>.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="tip">
                            Tip: Even if a shift is not applicable, the column must still be present in the CSV.
                            You may leave the value empty.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Sample CSV</h2>
                        <table>
                            <thead>
                                <tr>
                                    <th>day</th>
                                    <th>day_check_in</th>
                                    <th>day_check_out</th>
                                    <th>night_check_in</th>
                                    <th>night_check_out</th>
                                    <th>grace</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Monday</td>
                                    <td>09:00</td>
                                    <td>17:00</td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td></td>
                                    <td>10</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr>
                                    <td>Tuesday</td>
                                    <td>09:00</td>
                                    <td>17:00</td>
                                    <td>22:00</td>
                                    <td>06:00</td>
                                    <td>5</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>

                        <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Using invalid day names (e.g. <em>Mon</em>, <em>Fri</em>, <em>Holiday</em>)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Entering only one night shift time without the other
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Removing unused columns instead of leaving them empty
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Using incorrect time formats (e.g. 9:00 AM, 17.00)
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Setting grace values outside the range 0–60
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="error">
                            NOTE: Uploading a new schedule will <b>replace the existing schedule</b> for your
                            organization.
                            Make sure all required days are included in the CSV.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="face-upload font-styling" id="face-upload">
                        <h1><i class="fa-solid fa-4"></i> | Face Image Upload Guide</h1>

                        <p>
                            This image will be used for <b>face verification and attendance</b>.
                            Please upload a clear and accurate photo to ensure reliable recognition.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Image Requirements</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                The image must contain <b>only one person</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The face must be <b>clearly visible</b> and facing the camera.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                The image should be <b>well-lit</b> (avoid shadows or very dim lighting).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <b>No masks, sunglasses, or face coverings</b>.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Avoid blurry, pixelated, or low-quality images.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>Recommended Guidelines</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Neutral facial expression (no exaggerated expressions).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Plain or simple background is preferred.
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Face should occupy a reasonable portion of the image (not too far or too close).
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                Use a recent photo that reflects your current appearance.
                            </li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="tip">
                            Tip: A front-facing mobile camera photo taken in daylight usually works best.
                        </p>

                        <h2>Allowed File Types</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li><b>JPG / JPEG</b></li>
                            <li><b>PNG</b></li>
                        </ul>

                        <h2>Common Reasons for Rejection</h2>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Multiple faces detected in the image</li>
                            <li>Face partially covered (mask, scarf, hand, hair)</li>
                            <li>Side-face or tilted head</li>
                            <li>Very dark or overexposed images</li>
                            <li>Edited, filtered, or AI-generated images</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p class="error">
                            NOTE: Uploading an unclear or incorrect image may cause face verification
                            failures during attendance. Please upload carefully.
                        </p>
                    </div>

